<h2 data-size="r">The art of repair</h2>

<p class="alt-lede">Inspired by Kintsugi&#8212;the art of repairing broken pottery with gold&#8212;cracks aren&#8217;t hidden; they&#8217;re honored as part of your story.</p>

<p><a href="approach.html">Read about my approach</a></p>

</div><!-- item-section -->

<hr>

<div class="item-section" id="section-2">
<h1 data-size="r">Holding space</h1>

<p class="alt-lede">Session after session, whether you are absorbing grief, trauma, conflict, and complexity that most people never witness or holding the structural weight of an entire team, that burden doesn’t disappear when the hour or day ends. It follows you into your relationships, your rest, your body, and your sense of who you are.</p>

<p><a href="holding-space.html">Read about holding space</a></p>
</div><!-- item-section -->

<hr>

<div class="item-section" id="section-3">
<h2 data-size="r">Beyond supervision</h2>

<p class="alt-lede">Clinical supervision is essential, but not enough. Traditional supervision centers on managing the complexity of the case, not the complexity of the clinician.</p>

<p><a href="beyond-supervision.html">Read about beyond supervision</a></p>
</div><!-- item-section -->
    
<hr>
    
<div class="item-section" id="section-4">
<h2 data-size="r">A bridge between the work and the self</h2>

<p class="alt-lede">Even with a supportive team, most mental health practitioners carry a quiet sense of professional isolation. What’s missing is the bridge between the work and the self.</p>

<p><a href="bridge.html">Learn more about this bridge of support</a></p>

</div><!-- item-section -->

<hr>

<div class="item-section" id="section-5">
<h2 data-size="r">Integration is the goal</h2>

<p class="alt-lede">Together, we explore cultural identity, emotional patterns, history, and values. Not to return you to who you were, but to help you integrate into who you&#8217;re becoming.</p>

</div><!-- item-section -->


